   "source": [
    "# IRAS-SDLC Demo: End-to-End Risk Assessment\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the complete IRAS-SDLC pipeline:\n",
    "1. Load the IRAS dataset with pre-computed V, E, I scores\n",
    "2. Apply risk aggregation: R = αV + βE + γI\n",
    "3. Classify risks into Low/Medium/High\n",
    "4. Evaluate performance metrics\n",
    "5. Visualize results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append('..')\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.models.risk_aggregation import IRASRiskEngine\n",
    "from src.evaluation.metrics import IRASMetrics\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set style\n",
    "sns.set_style('whitegrid')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10, 6)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Load IRAS Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset contains pre-computed scores:\n",
    "- **V**: Vulnerability likelihood from CodeBERT [0, 1]\n",
    "- **E**: Exploitability score from CVSS [0, 1]\n",
    "- **I**: Impact score from CVSS [0, 1]\n",
    "- **R**: Pre-computed risk (for validation)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load dataset\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../data/iras_dataset.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset size: {len(df):,} samples\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nColumns: {df.columns.tolist()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFirst 5 rows:\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Summary statistics\n",
    "df.describe()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Initialize Risk Aggregation Engine\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll use the default balanced configuration:\n",
    "- α = 0.5 (Vulnerability likelihood)\n",
    "- β = 0.3 (Exploitability)\n",
    "- γ = 0.2 (Impact)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize engine with balanced weights\n",
    "engine = IRASRiskEngine(alpha=0.5, beta=0.3, gamma=0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Risk Engine Configuration:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  α (Vulnerability): {engine.alpha}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  β (Exploitability): {engine.beta}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  γ (Impact): {engine.gamma}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Compute Unified Risk Scores\n",
    "\n",
    "Apply R = αV + βE + γI to all samples"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extract V, E, I from dataset\n",
    "V = df['V'].values\n",
    "E = df['E'].values\n",
    "I = df['I'].values\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute unified risk\n",
    "R_computed = engine.aggregate_risk(V, E, I)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Classify risk levels\n",
    "risk_levels = [engine.classify_risk_level(r)[0] for r in R_computed]\n",
    "actions = [engine.classify_risk_level(r)[1] for r in R_computed]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add to dataframe\n",
    "df['R_computed'] = R_computed\n",
    "df['risk_level'] = risk_levels\n",
    "df['action'] = actions\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Risk scores computed successfully!\")\n",
    "df[['V', 'E', 'I', 'R_computed', 'risk_level', 'action']].head(10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Risk Distribution Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Count risk levels\n",
    "risk_counts = df['risk_level'].value_counts()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Risk Level Distribution:\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 40)\n",
    "for level in ['Low', 'Medium', 'High']:\n",
    "    count = risk_counts.get(level, 0)\n",
    "    pct = (count / len(df)) * 100\n",
    "    print(f\"{level:8s}: {count:6,d} ({pct:5.1f}%)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 40)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize risk distribution\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pie chart\n",
    "colors = ['#97C459', '#FAC775', '#F09595']\n",
    "axes[0].pie(risk_counts, labels=risk_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', \n",
    "            colors=colors, startangle=90)\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Risk Level Distribution', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Histogram of risk scores\n",
    "axes[1].hist(df['R_computed'], bins=50, edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "axes[1].axvline(0.4, color='green', linestyle='--', label='Low/Medium threshold')\n",
    "axes[1].axvline(0.7, color='red', linestyle='--', label='Medium/High threshold')\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Risk Score (R)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Frequency', fontsize=12)\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Risk Score Distribution', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "axes[1].grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Component Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Visualize how V, E, I contribute to the final risk"
